{"build_type":"library","description":"Parse a getdents64 buffer block into an array of {name,type} objects. Per linux_dirent64: d_reclen is the 2-byte LE field at off+16, d_type the byte at off+18, d_name the NUL-terminated string at off+19. Each kept entry's name is CLONED into the arena (clone-string-inside-memory-arena) before the text node is built, because encode-textual-payload-document-value aliases the supplied pointer and the getdents scratch buffer is a module-global reused for every directory in a recursive walk: without the clone, every held entry name dangles into the scratch buffer and is silently overwritten by the next directory listing. Skips the . and .. entries (so callers never recurse into them = no directory cycle). Captures d_type cheaply from getdents (no per-entry stat). Tail-recurses over records by off+reclen. Reuses clone_string_inside_memory_arena, compare_two_strings_byte_by_byte, begin_empty_mapping_document_value, encode_textual_payload_document_value, attach_named_member_inside_mapping, add_number_to_object, append_element_extending_document_sequence.","module_name":"collect-directory-entry-block-bearing-classification","package_name":"collect-directory-entry-block-bearing-classification","function_definitions":{"collect-directory-entry-block-bearing-classification":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"buf","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"off","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"nbytes","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"arr","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c16","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c17","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_tar